rots, apple, onion, rice wine vinegar, soy sauce, honey, mirin, sesame oil, orange juice, olive oil, cashews, celery salt, salt and pepper and chop <b>3 sec\/speed 5<b>, if necessary chop a further <b>2 sec\/speed 4.5<b>. Transfer to a large serving bowl and set aside."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Steamed Green Tea Salmon"},{"content":"Place a bowl onto mixing bowl lid. Weigh in salmon, rice wine vinegar, mirin, coriander, salt, white pepper and sugar. Coat each piece of salmon and set aside for 5-10 minutes to marinate."},{"content":"Place lemon peel, ginger and lemongrass into mixing bowl and grind <b>8 sec\/speed 8<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula."},{"content":"Add green tea powder and water to mixing bowl. Place reserved marinated salmon into Varoma dish and tray, scrape any excess marinade into mixing bowl. Set Varoma into position, secure Varoma lid and steam <b>14 min\/Varoma\/speed 2<b>. Serve with a wedge of lemon and the Asian Slaw."}],"hintsAndTricks":["If your salmon is not in 4 equal fillets and you have 4-6 pieces; arrange largest\/thickest pieces in Varoma dish and smaller\/thinner pieces on Varoma tray. Steaming time depends on the thickness of your fillets, steam a further few minutes if necessary.","Green tea powder is also known as matcha powder."],"basicInfo":["easy","50m","1h 20m","4 portions"]}